-- Treasury Secretary Geithner in Hospital for Surgery to Remove Kidney Stone
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2010-12-10T16:15:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/geithner-warns-republicans-against-politicizing-the-fed.html
U.S. Treasury Secretary  Timothy F. Geithner  was hospitalized today to have surgery to remove a
kidney stone.  Geithner “was admitted to George Washington University
Hospital this morning for treatment of a kidney stone,”
Treasury spokesman Steve Adamske said in a statement. “He will
have a minor surgical procedure this afternoon to remove the
kidney stone, and his physician expects that he will be
discharged tomorrow with orders to rest this weekend. He has
been told that he should expect to be able to return to work on
Monday.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Ian Katz  in Washington at 
 ikatz2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
